x4freetext: For short-lived fission products, nitrate solutions
of 245Cm (~ 1 ug) sealed in polypropylene tubes were
irradiated in the reactor CIRUS for 60 sec using
pneumatic carrier facility at a flux of 5 x 10**12
targets of 245Cm (~ 4 ug) covered with 0.025 mm thick
aluminum foils were irradiated in the reactor APSARA
for 20-200 min at a flux of 1.2 x 10**12 n/cm2/sec.
80 cm3 detector connected to a PC based 4096
The resolution of the detector system was 2.0 keV at
dead time of the detector system (<10%)
